Key Learning Points
type="password" only hides characters visually.
Password fields should never contain existing passwords.
Sensitive secrets should never be sent back to the client.
Access control flaws become far more dangerous when combined with information disclosure.
Pentester's Perspective
Whenever you encounter password update forms:

Inspect the HTML source.
Check for a value= attribute.
Verify whether another user's account page can be accessed.
Remember that masking is not encryption.
This combination of IDOR and password disclosure can lead directly to full account compromise.

